  "text": "Many centres in Poland -public and private health care institutions -perform surgeries within breast reconstruction. In recent years, the leading centres more and more often successfully perform mastectomy with areola incision, removing the entire gland with areola and nipple and sparing own breast skin (skin-sparing mastectomy). A necessary element of such a procedure is immediate reconstruction with the use of own tissues or implants -expander prostheses [CITATION_1] . A further development of this method is an areolasparing mastectomy -breast and nipple are removed -skin and areola are left [CITATION_2] . Such a procedure should take place in reference centres in which it is possible to conduct very detailed post-surgery tests in preinvasive cancer, or during prophylactic mastectomy [7] .",
